CKI Offers $3.9 Billion for Northumbrian Water, Telegraph Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-10T21:28:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-10/cki-offers-3-9-billion-for-northumbrian-water-telegraph-says.html
Northumbrian Water Group Plc (NWG) ’s board
met on July 7 to discuss an offer of about 2.4 billion pounds
($3.9 billion), or 460 pence a share, from Li Ka-shing’s  Cheung
Kong Infrastructure Holdings Ltd. (1038) , the  Daily Telegraph  reported,
citing unidentified sources.  The U.K. utility, advised by  Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) , has told
Cheung Kong it can carry out due diligence, the Telegraph said.
Northumbrian Water declined to comment and Cheung Kong
Infrastructure couldn’t be reached, the Telegraph said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 